# Rust build artifacts. Cargo.lock is intentionally tracked: this
# crate is published from the monorepo, and tracking the lockfile
# guarantees CI reproducibility between branch builds and the
# eventual `cargo publish` step. The Rust guidelines that "libraries
# should not commit Cargo.lock" assume the crate is the root of its
# own repo with no CI; for a monorepo SDK we want the same lockfile
# every developer sees locally and CI sees in `rust-sdk`.
/target/
